tional Considerations for Studies of ETUs ... 26 \n7.1 Eligible External ETUs ... 26 \n7.2 Internal Controllable ETUs ... 26 \n7.3 Non-controllable ETUs Involving Specified Equipment Additions without Associated \nSpecified Objectives ... 27 \n7.4 ETUs Involving Specified Objectives ... 27 \n8.0 Operational Considerations ... 27 \n9.0 Additional Considerations for Generating Facilities that include Storage ... 27 \n10.0 Cluster Studies ... 28 \n10.1 Cluster Study Overview ... 28 \n10.2 Cluster Study Milestones and Timeline ... 28 \n10.3 Cluster Study Process ... 30 \n10.3.1 Phase 1: Perform Required Analyses and Identify All Violations ... 31 \n10.3.2 Phase 2: Identify the Set of Upgrades to Address All Violations ... 33 \n10.3.2.1 Alternative Transmission Technologies ... 33 \n10.4 Phase 3: Calculate Cost Allocations for Required Upgrades ... 34 \n10.4.1 Upgrade Classifications ... 34 \n10.4.2 Cost Allocation Calculation Details for System Network Upgrades ... 36 \n10.4.3 Impact Calculations to Address Short Circuit Violations ... 36 \n10.4.4 Impact Calculations to Address Thermal Violations ... 37 \n10.4.5 Impact Calculations to Address Steady-State Voltage Violations ... 37 \n10.4.6 Impact Calculations to Address Stability Violations ... 38 \n10.4.7 Impact Calculations to Address Violations Identified Through an Analysis that is not a \nShort Circuit, Steady-State Thermal, Steady-State Voltage and Stability Analysis ... 38 \n11.0 State Jurisdictional Affected System Operator (ASO) Studies ... 38 \n11.1 State Jurisdictional ASO Studies Overview ... 38 \n11.2 Sate Jurisdictional ASO Scope and Study Report Review Timing ... 39 \n11.3 Coordination of State Jurisdictional ASO Studies with ISO Interconnection Studies ... 40 \n11.4 Coordination of State Jurisdictional ASO Studies with ISO Interconnection Studies – \nPost Order No. 2023 ... 40 \n\nISO-NE Public 5 \n11.4.1 Coordination of State Jurisdictional ASO Studies with the Transition Cluster Study \n(TCS) ... 41 \n11.4.1.1 State Jurisdictional ASO Studies Completing Before the Beginning of the TCS .41 \n11.4.1.2 Coordination of State Jurisdictional ASO Studies with the TCS ... 41 \n11.4.1.3 Coordination of State Jurisdictional ASO Studies with the TCS – Timing ... 41 \n11.4.2 State Jurisdictional ASO Study Coordination After Transition ... 43 \n11.4.2.1 State Jurisdictional ASO Studies Completing Before the Beginning of the ISO \nCluster Study ... 43 \n11.4.2.2 Coordination of State Jurisdictional ASO Studies with the ISO Cluster Study ... 44 \n11.4.2.3 Coordination of State Jurisdictional ASO Studies with the ISO Cluster Study – \nTiming ... 44 \n11.4.2.4 Coordination of State Jurisdictional ASO Studies with the ISO Cluster Restudy 44 \n11.5 State Jurisdictional Project Clustering Milestones ... 45 \nAppendix A – General Transmission System Design Requirements for the Interconnection of \nNew Generating Facilities and ETUs to the Administered Transmission System ... 49 \nAppendix B – Requirements of PSS/E Models ... 51 \nAppendix C – Requirements of Electromagnetic Transient (EMT) Models ... 54 \nAppendix D – Detailed Considerations for the Study of an Inverter Based Generating Facility..55 \nAppendix E – Procedures for Material Modification Determinations ... 57 \nAppendix F – IEEE 2800 Requirements ... 61 \nAppendix G – Cost Allocation Methodology Examples ... 64 \nAppendix H – Site Control Considerations, Including Regulatory Limitations and Acreage \nRequirements ... 82 \nAppendix I – Determination Procedure for New or Increased Generation >1MW and <5 MW ..84 \n\nAttachments Appendix C-1 Electromagnetic Transient Modeling Requirements Appendix C-2 Model Acceptance Tests for Inverter-Based Resources\n\nINTERCONNECTION PROCEDURE FOR GENERATION AND ELECTIVE TRANSMISSION UPGRADES\n\n1.0 Introduction \nThe purpose of this procedure is to describe the scope of Interconnection Studies conducted pursuant to \nSchedule 22 (“Large Generator Interconnection Procedures” or “LGIP”), 